data.value:
~Image Matching Application~
This applications allows the users to verify if two images are the same or not. For running this applications you must follow this steps:
Step 1 > Upload two images using the buttons Upload photo 1 and Upload photo 2 from the tab "Upload photos"; (WARNING! if the images aren't uploaded the application will not pass to the next step)
Step 2 > Select the method you want for obtaining the pixels values from the photos in tab "Choose values" *Random method, button PixelRandom (it allows to generate n values <where n is a number obtained by selecting it from the trackbar next to the button> of coordinates in a random way. and display them as there associated values for each of the two photos ) *Star method, buton PixelStar (it allows to generate value from the main diagonal, the secundar diagonal and the vertical and horizontal line from the middle of the picture) *Combined method <the two from above>, button Pixel R+S (it allows to generate values obtained by combining the methods descripted above)
Step 3 > Select the method to detect the matching level of the pictures in tab "Matching Detection" *Euclid distance method *Minkowski distance method *Bray - Curtis distance method
